ript is being passed as a single argument to `/bin/sh -c`, so the entire multi-line command including the while loop should execute, but the logs are only showing the initial echo statement. Let me try executing directly into the container to see what's actually running and whether the scaling events are being logged. I could try checking the pod's log file directly or use `kubectl exec` to see what's happening in the loop, but honestly the most practical approach is to just verify the scaling actually occurred by looking at the deployment events instead of relying on logs that might be delayed or cached.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":913,"cache_read_input_tokens":33398,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":913},"output_tokens":47,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4bf6e6d7-1b6a-4464-9944-44187292fe60","uuid":"44e1b80e-f038-4b6d-8aa5-def6cf36f29f","request_id":"req_011CcgVw2K16n3QEwkACdMrL"}
